{{pp-move-indef}}{{calendar}}
{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*   [[8]] &ndash; [[Roman Empire]] [[General officer|general]] [[Tiberius]] defeats [[Dalmatae]] on the river [[List of rivers of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bathinus]].
* [[435]] &ndash; Deposed [[Ecumenical Patriarch of Constantinople]] [[Nestorius]], considered the originator of [[Nestorianism]], is exiled by [[List of Byzantine emperors|Roman Emperor]] [[Theodosius II]] to a [[monastery]] in [[Egypt]].
* [[881]] &ndash; [[Battle of Saucourt-en-Vimeu]]: [[Louis III of France]] defeats the [[Viking]]s, an event celebrated in the poem ''[[Ludwigslied]]''.
*[[1031]] &ndash; [[Olaf II of Norway]] is canonized as Saint Olaf by [[Grimketel]], the English [[Bishop of Selsey]].
*[[1342]] &ndash; The [[Siege of Algeciras (1342–1344)|Siege of Algeciras]] commences during the Spanish [[Reconquista]].
*[[1492]] &ndash; [[Christopher Columbus]] sets sail from [[Palos de la Frontera]], Spain.
*[[1527]] &ndash; The first known letter from North America is sent by [[John Rut]] while at [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St. John's, Newfoundland]].
*[[1601]] &ndash; [[Long War (Ottoman wars)|Long War]]: [[Habsburg Monarchy|Austria]] captures [[Transylvania]] in the [[Battle of Goroszló]].
*[[1645]] &ndash; [[Thirty Years' War]]: the [[Battle of Nördlingen (1645)|Second Battle of Nördlingen]] sees French forces defeating those of the [[Holy Roman Empire]].
*[[1678]] &ndash; [[René-Robert Cavelier, Sieur de La Salle|Robert LaSalle]] builds the ''[[Le Griffon]]'', the first known ship built on the [[Great Lakes]].
*[[1795]] &ndash; [[Treaty of Greenville]] is signed.
*[[1811]] &ndash; First ascent of [[Jungfrau]], third highest summit in the [[Bernese Alps]] by brothers Johann Rudolf and Hieronymus Meyer.
*[[1852]] &ndash;  [[Harvard University]] wins the first [[Harvard–Yale Regatta|Boat Race]] between [[Yale University]] and Harvard. The race is also the first American intercollegiate athletic event
*[[1860]] &ndash; The [[New Zealand Wars|Second Maori War]] begins in New Zealand.
*[[1900]] &ndash; The [[Firestone Tire and Rubber Company]] is founded.
*[[1903]] &ndash; [[Internal Macedonian Revolutionary Organization|Macedonian rebels]] in [[Kruševo]] proclaim the [[Kruševo Republic]], which exists only for 10 days before [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman Turks]] lay waste to the town.
*[[1907]] &ndash; Judge [[Kenesaw Mountain Landis]] fines [[Amoco|Standard Oil of Indiana]] a record $29.4 million for illegal rebating to freight carriers; the conviction and fine are later reversed on appeal.
*[[1913]] &ndash; A major labour dispute, known as the [[Wheatland Hop Riot]], starts in [[Wheatland, California]].
*[[1914]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: Germany declares war against France.
*[[1921]] &ndash; [[Commissioner of Baseball|Major League Baseball Commissioner]] [[Kenesaw Mountain Landis]] confirms the ban of the eight [[Black Sox Scandal|Chicago Black Sox]], the day after they were acquitted by a Chicago court.
*[[1929]] &ndash; [[Jiddu Krishnamurti]], tagged as the [[Messianism|messianic]] "[[Maitreya (Theosophy)|World Teacher]]", shocks the [[Theosophy]] movement by dissolving the [[Order of the Star in the East|Order of the Star]], the organisation built to support him.
*[[1934]] &ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] becomes the supreme leader of Germany by joining the offices of [[President of Germany (1919–1945)|President]] and [[Chancellor of Germany#Chancellor of the Third Reich (1933–1945)|Chancellor]] into ''[[Führer]]''.
*[[1936]] &ndash; [[Jesse Owens]] wins the 100 meter dash, defeating [[Ralph Metcalfe]], at the [[1936 Summer Olympics|Berlin Olympics]].
*  1936   &ndash; A fire wipes out [[Kursha-2]] in the [[Meshchera Lowlands]], [[Ryazan Oblast]], [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Russia]], killing 1,200 and leaving only 20 survivors.
*[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Kingdom of Italy|Italian]] forces begin the [[Italian conquest of British Somaliland|invasion of British Somaliland]].
*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Holiday World & Splashin' Safari|Santa Claus Land]], the world's first themed [[amusement park]], opens in [[Santa Claus, Indiana]], United States.
*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Whittaker Chambers]] accuses [[Alger Hiss]] of being a [[Communism|communist]] and a [[Espionage|spy]] for the [[Soviet Union]].
*[[1958]] &ndash; The [[nuclear submarine]] {{USS|Nautilus|SSN-571|6}} travels beneath the [[Arctic Ocean|Arctic]] ice cap.
*[[1959]] &ndash; Portugal's state police force [[PIDE]] [[Pidjiguiti Massacre|fires upon striking workers]] in [[Bissau]], [[Portuguese Guinea]], killing over 50 people.
*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Niger]] gains independence from France.
*[[1961]] &ndash; The [[New Democratic Party (Canada)|New Democratic Party]] of [[Canada]] is founded by the merger of the [[Cooperative Commonwealth Federation]] and the [[Canadian Labour Congress]].
*[[1972]] &ndash; The [[United States Senate]] ratifies the [[Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty]].
*[[1975]] &ndash; A privately chartered [[Boeing 707]] crashes into the mountainside near [[Agadir]], [[Morocco]], killing 188.
*[[1977]] &ndash; The United States Senate begins its hearing on [[Project MKUltra]].
*  1977   &ndash; [[Tandy Corporation]] announces the [[TRS-80]], one of the world's first mass-produced [[personal computer]]s.
*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Senegal]]ese opposition parties, under the leadership of [[Mamadou Dia]], launch the [[Antiimperialist Action Front – Suxxali Reew Mi]].
*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Oued El-Had and Mezouara massacre]] in [[Algeria]]; a total of 116 villagers killed, 40 in Oued El-Had and 76 in Mezouara.
*[[2001]] &ndash; The [[Real Irish Republican Army|Real IRA]] [[2001 Ealing bombing|detonates a car bomb]] in [[Ealing]], [[London|London, England]], United Kingdom injuring seven people.
*[[2004]] &ndash; The pedestal of the [[Statue of Liberty]] reopens after being closed since the [[September 11 attacks]].
*[[2005]] &ndash; [[List of heads of state of Mauritania|President of Mauritania]] [[Maaouya Ould Sid'Ahmed Taya]] is overthrown in a [[Coup d'état|military coup]] while attending the funeral of [[Fahd of Saudi Arabia|King Fahd]] in [[Saudi Arabia]].
*  2005   &ndash; [[Mahmoud Ahmadinejad]] becomes [[President of Iran]].
*[[2007]] &ndash; Former Deputy Director of the [[Dirección de Inteligencia Nacional|Chilean secret police]] [[Raúl Iturriaga]] is captured after having been on the run following a conviction for [[kidnapping]].
*[[2010]] &ndash; [[2010 Karachi riots|Widespread rioting]] erupts in [[Karachi]], [[Pakistan]], after the assassination of a local politician, leaving at least 85 dead and at least 17 billion [[Pakistani rupee]]s ([[United States dollar|US$]]200 million) in damage.

